                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=michael.heuberger",
                        "name": "michael.heuberger",
                        "displayName": "Michael Heuberger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Probably this isn't a bug. But can you give at least subclasses a chance to tell the constructor in which indexes of $_SERVER it should parse for any indications that the current request is a SSL one?\r\n\r\nProbably a protected method returning an array, by default array('HTTPS') which could be overwritten in my subclass with array('HTTPS', 'HTTP_SCHEME')\r\n\r\nThanks!",
